Package se.idsec.cose

Class Signer

java.lang.Object
se.idsec.cose.Attribute
se.idsec.cose.Signer
Direct Known Subclasses:
CounterSign, CounterSign1
public class Signer extends Attribute
The Signer class is used to implement the COSE_Signer object. This provides the information dealing with a single signature for the SignCOSEObject class.

Create a Signer object for adding a new signature to a message, existing signers will have a Signer object created for them when a SignCOSEObject object is created by COSEObject.DecodeFromBytes.

Examples of using this class can be found in
Single Signer Example an example of signing and verify a message with a single signature.
Multiple Signer Example an example of signing and verifying a message which has multiple signatures.

Author:
jimsch
